titleproper.value:
Guide to the Records of the RISM 
                    <lb/>Medical School Attitude Questionnaire (MSAQ)
                    <lb/>
                    <num>RISM RG 7</num>

author.value: Finding aid prepared by Inventory prepared by Margaret Fraser and Samantha Gibson, September 2010.

creation.value:
This finding aid was produced using the Archivists' Toolkit
                <date>2016-01-19T16:48-0500</date>

unittitle.value: Records of the RISM Medical School Attitude Questionnaire (MSAQ)

abstract.label: Abstract
abstract.value: Conducted between 1959 and 1960, the Medical Students Attitude Questionnaire was a cross-cultural study undertaken by the Research Institute for the Study of Man (RISM) and the World Federation on Mental Health, which examined the beliefs and feelings medical students had toward a variety of issues pertaining to their future roles as medical professionals. The materials include correspondence, questionnaires, and responses.

p.value:
Additionally, please note that this collection is stored 
                <extref ns2:href="http://www.nyu.edu/library/bobst/research/arch/medicalRISM.htm">
                    <archref> offsite </archref> </extref>, and you must contact the repository to schedule access.
[Identification of item, Date(s) if known] The Medical Student Attitude Questionnaire RISM RG 7, Box and Folder Number(s) New York University Archives Elmer Holmes Bobst Library

The questionnaire was administered to students in many parts of the world, including Austria, Belgium, Canada, Chile, France, Germany, Great Britain, Mexico, Peru, the Philippines, and the United States.

Series III: Questionnaires contains a bulk of the contents and is comprised of completed questionnaires by medical students from universities around the world and some blank copies of the questionnaires. The questionnaires have been grouped by the part of the world or specific institution where they were completed.
